Run the commands:

<lsquant-path>/lsquant-official/build/inline_compute-kpm-MeanSquareDisplacement_Graphene_NNN_2 100 500 10 100 0

<lsquant-path>/lsquant-official/build/device-postProcess_Graphene_NNN




OVERVIEW:
This will run the Aron case for the specific random puddle distribution initialized with seed 3.


BREAKDOWN OF THE COMMANDS:
<lsquant-path>/lsquant-official/build/inline_compute-kpm-MeanSquareDisplacement_Graphene_NNN_2 <D> <N_MOM> <N_TSTEPS> <T_MAX>


   D: Number of graphene unit cells in each direction of the superlattice
      ( the superlattice will be DxD)
   N_MOM: Number of Chebyshev polynomials in the DOS expansion
   N_TSTEPS: Number of time steps of the time evolution
   T_MAX: maximum time of the time evolution





ARON RESULTS:
To reproduce Aron results exactly, run the following (computation will take a day or two):


<lsquant-path>/lsquant-official/build/inline_compute-kpm-MeanSquareDisplacement_Graphene_NNN_2 1000 7000 50 5000

<lsquant-path>/lsquant-oficial/build/device-postProcess_Graphene_NNN
